      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_medicine_clinical_l3_proximal_humerus_fractures",
      "content": {
        "title": "Proximal Humerus Fractures — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Fractures of the surgical neck and tuberosities of the proximal humerus, classified by fragment number and displacement.",
        "summary": "Neer classification guides treatment. Low-demand elderly patients may be managed nonoperatively; displaced multi-part fractures often require ORIF or arthroplasty."
      },
